In the spring of this year, everything started from scratch when the MGM team began with the restructuring plan, which was finally signed by the creditors at the end of October after months of debate and internal disputes.
If MGM has officially survived bankruptcy in the next few weeks, Moelis and Cooper will receive a multi-million dollar bonus for their work.
The share for Moelis & Co., which has already received $1.2 million, amounts to $9.5 million.
Cooper, who was paid $375,000 a month to run the company, will receive a “success bonus” of $4 million.
Barber and Birnbaum are planning to resume production at MGM. This year, the studio released only one film and created an annual plan with seven or eight films to be released in early 2012.
