The studio needs a separate bond between $265 million and $275 million for its financial stake in these two films, which are to be produced under the direction of Peter Jackson.
Investor Carl Icahn, who has financed about 18% of the MGM loan, attempted a merger of the studio with Lions Gate Entertainment, whose largest shareholder he is.
However, the last negotiations between the two companies resulted in no results.
