What will be the consequences of this defamation inflicted on such a tremendous power?
It is obvious that in the future the states will no longer provide any reserved information online - this would be like a hangover stuck on the street corner.
But it’s equally obvious that it’s futile to hope with current technologies to keep confidential reports over the phone.
Nothing is easier than figuring out if and when a head of state is moving in an airplane and has contacted one of his colleagues.
In the future, how could certain relationships be maintained privately and only for certain ears?
I know very well that my prediction at the moment sounds like science fiction and novelty, but I see myself forced to imagine the government agents, moving in a secret way, deliberately on uncontrollable marching routes, carrying their messages nowhere but in mere memory, carrying the information with them, and beyond.
The information would be stored in a single copy in closed drawers: basically Watergate’s espionage attempt was less successful than WikiLeaks.
