In addition, the minced steak, the tuna from the can, even the baguette and the chewing gum were spiked with pesticides and other chemical substances.
In the tap water, the analyses have revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
At dinner, the salmon steak with 34 identified chemical residues was the "richest", and even the plastic plate used to warm up the meal in the microwave was not unloaded.
The ultimate risk of this “pollutant cocktail” to the consumer “is likely to be underestimated,” the study said.
The Alliance Europe Ecologie-Les Verts (EE-LV) has, for its part, proposed a moratorium on the use of pesticides to stop the "growth of civilisational diseases".
